{"_id":"07ByXWPoykuejm9e","name":"The Green Knight","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"OK3cqMatnCypt0tz","name":"The Green Knight - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Green Knight","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 192.","positive":"I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Green Knight","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bOqrdY4uPIMVpk3D","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Green Knight","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease. \nAgenda: Protect the altar and allow those who worship the \nold gods to have a place to worship. \nGift - The Just Punishment: The Green Knight starts \neach Scene with 3 Retaliation Tokens, each time he suffers \n1 Wound he can spend 1 Token to inflict 1 Wound on whoever hit him.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 192.","owner":"The Green Knight","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-the-green-knight-192","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":192,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease. \nAgenda: Protect the altar and allow those who worship the \nold gods to have a place to worship. \nGift - The Just Punishment: The Green Knight starts \neach Scene with 3 Retaliation Tokens, each time he suffers \n1 Wound he can spend 1 Token to inflict 1 Wound on whoever hit him.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect the altar and allow those who worship the \nold gods to have a place to worship.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1Aw1B8926eTW8q99","name":"Robbers","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1Lfx2JClg7Kv6amF","name":"Robbers - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Robbers","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 140.","positive":"We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Robbers","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sbMXEQLWPL5QlCQG","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Robbers","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.\nInformation: There are no rooms to sleep in at the Tavern, which is best known for the haute cuisine of Chef Brigit. Nobles and rich men come from all over Europe to taste \nthe food of the Golden Plate. Brigit became accustomed to \nBastian’s presence, always showering her with compliments on her cooking. At first, Bastian was a good customer, \nbut soon he had no money to pay for the meals, and Brigit \ngave him credit until she realized that the soldier was a lost \ncause. If asked about Bastian, Brigit will say that he is a good-tempered man who tries to live far beyond his means. \nWhen he is not eating at the Golden Plate, Bastian is often \nat the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House, where he gambles and tries to accumulate some money.\nIf Bastian is present: He will sit at the table and beg \nBrigit to serve him one of her fantastic dishes. As soon as \nhe sees the Hunters, he will try to escape by sneaking into \nthe kitchens.\nIf the Black Cat is present: The Hunters will see her \nthrough the half-open door into the kitchen as she tries to \nknock down an old ladle hanging on the wall with her paw. \nThe Cat is unsuccessful, as someone always intervenes to \nchase it away. Brigit will complain that the animal seems \nto be obsessed with the old ladle given to her by the elderly \nBritta. \nFirst Reset: If this is the first time he encounters the \nHunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, \nif the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not \nappear again.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 140.","owner":"Robbers","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-robbers-140","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":140,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.\nInformation: There are no rooms to sleep in at the Tavern, which is best known for the haute cuisine of Chef Brigit. Nobles and rich men come from all over Europe to taste \nthe food of the Golden Plate. Brigit became accustomed to \nBastian’s presence, always showering her with compliments on her cooking. At first, Bastian was a good customer, \nbut soon he had no money to pay for the meals, and Brigit \ngave him credit until she realized that the soldier was a lost \ncause. If asked about Bastian, Brigit will say that he is a good-tempered man who tries to live far beyond his means. \nWhen he is not eating at the Golden Plate, Bastian is often \nat the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House, where he gambles and tries to accumulate some money.\nIf Bastian is present: He will sit at the table and beg \nBrigit to serve him one of her fantastic dishes. As soon as \nhe sees the Hunters, he will try to escape by sneaking into \nthe kitchens.\nIf the Black Cat is present: The Hunters will see her \nthrough the half-open door into the kitchen as she tries to \nknock down an old ladle hanging on the wall with her paw. \nThe Cat is unsuccessful, as someone always intervenes to \nchase it away. Brigit will complain that the animal seems \nto be obsessed with the old ladle given to her by the elderly \nBritta. \nFirst Reset: If this is the first time he encounters the \nHunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, \nif the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not \nappear again.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1fO3397r07ryycl9","name":"The Magic Lake Portal","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"hCBX236xjFaC5HOj","name":"The Magic Lake Portal - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Magic Lake Portal","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218.","positive":"A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Magic Lake Portal","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"P4eY9hMSgLkfxR6N","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Magic Lake Portal","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218.","owner":"The Magic Lake Portal","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-the-magic-lake-portal-218","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":218,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2QCyVC62tCz7fvT5","name":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jSRHT04V3sVhJnyM","name":"Ivory Seeking Pirates - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158.","positive":"We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642442,"modifiedTime":1781557642442,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TQXMB9Fk3Xf2jJbb","name":"Gift - Pirate Crew","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A Pirate increases their OL by 1 when \nthe Captain is present. \nCaptain of the Ivory Seeking \nPirates</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642442,"modifiedTime":1781557642442,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bD5CvMOeWobnjgsu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns. \nAgenda: Obey the captain’s orders. \nGift - Pirate Crew: A Pirate increases their OL by 1 when \nthe Captain is present. \nCaptain of the Ivory Seeking \nPirates</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158.","owner":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642442,"modifiedTime":1781557642442,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-ivory-seeking-pirates-158","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns. \nAgenda: Obey the captain’s orders. \nGift - Pirate Crew: A Pirate increases their OL by 1 when \nthe Captain is present. \nCaptain of the Ivory Seeking \nPirates</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Obey the captain’s orders.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642458,"modifiedTime":1781557642458,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3SLSu4vZsbehoJ9o","name":"3: Mikko","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"I24ejMCYjQbZ9WvA","name":"3: Mikko - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"3: Mikko","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119.","positive":"I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"3: Mikko","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jHfoaf12lgfifrkx","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"3: Mikko","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 \nWound)\nDescriptor: I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants. \nAgenda: Make the village prosperous and \nearn good money. \nInformation: Mikko is the newest addition \nto the group of elders and was not present during the first \nnight of the pledge. He does not believe in rumors and sees \nthe “kidnapped” people simply as workers who choose to \nstay in the comfort of Nikola’s warm and cozy mansion. \nHowever, Mikko noticed that some of the traders missed \nthe appointment to load the gold and he has not heard \nfrom them. The old man has noted everything in his records, where it can be seen that the missed appointments \nand disappearances of the merchants occur on a regular basis. However, the old accountant is extremely jealous of his \nwork and will not share the records with anyone. \n4: Katri</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119.","owner":"3: Mikko","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-3-mikko-119","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":119,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 \nWound)\nDescriptor: I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants. \nAgenda: Make the village prosperous and \nearn good money. \nInformation: Mikko is the newest addition \nto the group of elders and was not present during the first \nnight of the pledge. He does not believe in rumors and sees \nthe “kidnapped” people simply as workers who choose to \nstay in the comfort of Nikola’s warm and cozy mansion. \nHowever, Mikko noticed that some of the traders missed \nthe appointment to load the gold and he has not heard \nfrom them. The old man has noted everything in his records, where it can be seen that the missed appointments \nand disappearances of the merchants occur on a regular basis. However, the old accountant is extremely jealous of his \nwork and will not share the records with anyone. \n4: Katri</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Make the village prosperous and \nearn good money.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3pl4aKy7zqZsNrCD","name":"The Imposter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"gcMqtPDWQyQg50sr","name":"The Imposter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Imposter","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","positive":"I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Imposter","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YIJsiEfpcSAUjuXB","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Imposter","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.\nAgenda: To keep the life that was gifted to me. I am not evil \nand therefore I can play the role of the good Hazir well. \nThe Four Daughters of Hazir</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","owner":"The Imposter","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-imposter-163","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.\nAgenda: To keep the life that was gifted to me. I am not evil \nand therefore I can play the role of the good Hazir well. \nThe Four Daughters of Hazir</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To keep the life that was gifted to me. I am not evil \nand therefore I can play the role of the good Hazir well. \nThe Four Daughters of Hazir","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"69fMuRE1MWgFizKt","name":"Haunted House","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Sw9VvrH7OYYyxO3c","name":"Haunted House - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Haunted House","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 206.","positive":"A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Haunted House","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pxIis2ZzKokk89wT","name":"Gift - Induced Fatigue","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Haunted House","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>For each room visited in the \nHouse, roll one die for each intruder:\n1-3: Nothing happens.\n4-6: They lose 1 Soma. \nOn the second point of Soma lost to this Gift, a Hunter \nmust pass a Defense Check to avoid falling into an eighthour deep sleep from which they cannot be awakened. For \nan NPC, the effect is triggered when they lose Soma equal \nto the category of their OL: 1 for Easy, 2 for Medium, and \n3 for Hard.\nFlora’s Bedroom</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 206.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Haunted House","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LX0TYO5vIec48WR8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Haunted House","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep. \nGift - Induced Fatigue: For each room visited in the \nHouse, roll one die for each intruder:\n1-3: Nothing happens.\n4-6: They lose 1 Soma. \nOn the second point of Soma lost to this Gift, a Hunter \nmust pass a Defense Check to avoid falling into an eighthour deep sleep from which they cannot be awakened. For \nan NPC, the effect is triggered when they lose Soma equal \nto the category of their OL: 1 for Easy, 2 for Medium, and \n3 for Hard.\nFlora’s Bedroom\nDescriptor: A richly decorated room with a large canopy \nbed. Flowers and plants of all kinds grow on the walls, giving \nthe impression of being in a small greenhouse. \nInformation: The Hunters will quickly notice a small box \non the wardrobe next to the bed. Inside is Flora’s diary, but \nas you might guess, a witch’s box can’t be opened by just \nanyone.\n2a</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 206.","owner":"Haunted House","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-haunted-house-206","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":206,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep. \nGift - Induced Fatigue: For each room visited in the \nHouse, roll one die for each intruder:\n1-3: Nothing happens.\n4-6: They lose 1 Soma. \nOn the second point of Soma lost to this Gift, a Hunter \nmust pass a Defense Check to avoid falling into an eighthour deep sleep from which they cannot be awakened. For \nan NPC, the effect is triggered when they lose Soma equal \nto the category of their OL: 1 for Easy, 2 for Medium, and \n3 for Hard.\nFlora’s Bedroom\nDescriptor: A richly decorated room with a large canopy \nbed. Flowers and plants of all kinds grow on the walls, giving \nthe impression of being in a small greenhouse. \nInformation: The Hunters will quickly notice a small box \non the wardrobe next to the bed. Inside is Flora’s diary, but \nas you might guess, a witch’s box can’t be opened by just \nanyone.\n2a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6AgLmnl8Lczmtx8m","name":"Helpers","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"xAFHLOPyHrBC0y0t","name":"Helpers - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helpers","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125.","positive":"We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Helpers","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"H38dhLcwikSemqT2","name":"Gift - Servants of the Mansion","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helpers","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Each Helper can avail themselves of a different effect based on their role.\nJori the Cook: Can inflict 1 additional Wound with his \ncleaver. Injuries inflicted by Jori count as a mark for Nikola’s Reindeer.\nPete the Butler: When moving inside the mansion, Pete \nignores any movement penalty and no one can block him.\nVerna the Accountant: Increases her OL to Hard 7 \nwhen defending against an attack inside the mansion.\nNikola Lupei</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Helpers","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"n3x9skXcgKKYFq0D","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helpers","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them. \nAgenda: Defend Nikola from all threats.\nGift - Servants of the Mansion: Each Helper can avail themselves of a different effect based on their role.\nJori the Cook: Can inflict 1 additional Wound with his \ncleaver. Injuries inflicted by Jori count as a mark for Nikola’s Reindeer.\nPete the Butler: When moving inside the mansion, Pete \nignores any movement penalty and no one can block him.\nVerna the Accountant: Increases her OL to Hard 7 \nwhen defending against an attack inside the mansion.\nNikola Lupei</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125.","owner":"Helpers","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-helpers-125","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":125,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them. \nAgenda: Defend Nikola from all threats.\nGift - Servants of the Mansion: Each Helper can avail themselves of a different effect based on their role.\nJori the Cook: Can inflict 1 additional Wound with his \ncleaver. Injuries inflicted by Jori count as a mark for Nikola’s Reindeer.\nPete the Butler: When moving inside the mansion, Pete \nignores any movement penalty and no one can block him.\nVerna the Accountant: Increases her OL to Hard 7 \nwhen defending against an attack inside the mansion.\nNikola Lupei</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defend Nikola from all threats.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6YwAcsjsqkuM5V9y","name":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"SMoTjBAyD8S5Lcmr","name":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 164.","positive":"We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CT3R7dkranlCPpox","name":"Gift - Invincible Duo","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>While fighting as a pair, Fury \nand Wrath cannot take Wounds. Any attack or method of \nwounding them will be blocked by one of the two Djinn. \nTo avoid this Gift, it is necessary to use an effect that affects \nboth Djinn at the same time or to separate them so that \nthey cannot support each other. \n6B The Djinn King\nThe story that led us here...\nThe Hunters are summoned to the deck of the ship, where \nthey will find a mysterious old man smoking a water pipe. \nThe old man will ask them to run errands for him, and if they \ndo a good job, he will reward them with a golden Tarì. The \nold man exudes a strong aura of power, and the Hunters understand that the strange figure is hiding his true nature. The \nship lands on a large island and the old man claps his hands \nin satisfaction: it is time to begin. The Hunters must find nine \ngolden columns scattered throughout the city and bring them \nback to him so he can furnish his palace.\nPlace: A large port city filled with temples and merchant \ndistricts.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 164.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bHSUDnIGt5KrhL8g","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique. \nAgenda: Carry out every order of Hazir. \nGift - Invincible Duo: While fighting as a pair, Fury \nand Wrath cannot take Wounds. Any attack or method of \nwounding them will be blocked by one of the two Djinn. \nTo avoid this Gift, it is necessary to use an effect that affects \nboth Djinn at the same time or to separate them so that \nthey cannot support each other. \n6B The Djinn King\nThe story that led us here...\nThe Hunters are summoned to the deck of the ship, where \nthey will find a mysterious old man smoking a water pipe. \nThe old man will ask them to run errands for him, and if they \ndo a good job, he will reward them with a golden Tarì. The \nold man exudes a strong aura of power, and the Hunters understand that the strange figure is hiding his true nature. The \nship lands on a large island and the old man claps his hands \nin satisfaction: it is time to begin. The Hunters must find nine \ngolden columns scattered throughout the city and bring them \nback to him so he can furnish his palace.\nPlace: A large port city filled with temples and merchant \ndistricts.\nInformation: Finding the columns is only a matter of \ntime for the Hunters, but they will encounter several people \nwho need help. Even if they don’t know it, spending time \nwith others will earn the Hunters a positive rating from the \nDjinn King. \nChallenges: Each column requires 1 hour of time and at \nleast one Position Check. The list below shows where they \ncan be found. Using Gifts and Descriptors for additional information can speed up the search. For every two columns \nfound, roll 1 die to see who needs help, up to a maximum \nof 3 requests. \nThe Columns\nFirst: On the pier in the harbor, covered with seaweed and \nshells. / Second: In a dung-covered square used as a hitching post for horses and camels. / Third: In the inner courtyard of a merchant’s mansion. / Fourth: In the middle of \nan olive grove, not far from the city walls. / Fifth: In the art \ncollection of a wealthy Vizier. / Sixth: In the middle of a \nnotorious tavern, as a pillar supporting the roof. / Seventh: \nIn the wall of a watchtower. / Eighth: In the bedroom of the \nfirst daughter of the Sultan. / Ninth: In the hold of Sinbad’s \nship, stolen and then forgotten by the old sailor years ago.\nThe Needy\n1: A poor farmer has no money to buy seeds for the coming \nseason. Without the precious seeds, he will not be able to \nfeed his family. \n2: A child just five years old is lost and has wandered clear \nacross the city from where he lives. He struggles to speak \nand is frightened, but no one seems to care about him. \n3: A poor sailor was poisoned by some villains because he \nwon too much at dice. If he does not get an antidote he will \ndie. \n4: A merchant was robbed of a precious gold crown he \nhad bought for his daughter’s wedding. Without the crown,</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 164.","owner":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-fury-and-wrath-the-two-deadly-twins-164","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":164,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique. \nAgenda: Carry out every order of Hazir. \nGift - Invincible Duo: While fighting as a pair, Fury \nand Wrath cannot take Wounds. Any attack or method of \nwounding them will be blocked by one of the two Djinn. \nTo avoid this Gift, it is necessary to use an effect that affects \nboth Djinn at the same time or to separate them so that \nthey cannot support each other. \n6B The Djinn King\nThe story that led us here...\nThe Hunters are summoned to the deck of the ship, where \nthey will find a mysterious old man smoking a water pipe. \nThe old man will ask them to run errands for him, and if they \ndo a good job, he will reward them with a golden Tarì. The \nold man exudes a strong aura of power, and the Hunters understand that the strange figure is hiding his true nature. The \nship lands on a large island and the old man claps his hands \nin satisfaction: it is time to begin. The Hunters must find nine \ngolden columns scattered throughout the city and bring them \nback to him so he can furnish his palace.\nPlace: A large port city filled with temples and merchant \ndistricts.\nInformation: Finding the columns is only a matter of \ntime for the Hunters, but they will encounter several people \nwho need help. Even if they don’t know it, spending time \nwith others will earn the Hunters a positive rating from the \nDjinn King. \nChallenges: Each column requires 1 hour of time and at \nleast one Position Check. The list below shows where they \ncan be found. Using Gifts and Descriptors for additional information can speed up the search. For every two columns \nfound, roll 1 die to see who needs help, up to a maximum \nof 3 requests. \nThe Columns\nFirst: On the pier in the harbor, covered with seaweed and \nshells. / Second: In a dung-covered square used as a hitching post for horses and camels. / Third: In the inner courtyard of a merchant’s mansion. / Fourth: In the middle of \nan olive grove, not far from the city walls. / Fifth: In the art \ncollection of a wealthy Vizier. / Sixth: In the middle of a \nnotorious tavern, as a pillar supporting the roof. / Seventh: \nIn the wall of a watchtower. / Eighth: In the bedroom of the \nfirst daughter of the Sultan. / Ninth: In the hold of Sinbad’s \nship, stolen and then forgotten by the old sailor years ago.\nThe Needy\n1: A poor farmer has no money to buy seeds for the coming \nseason. Without the precious seeds, he will not be able to \nfeed his family. \n2: A child just five years old is lost and has wandered clear \nacross the city from where he lives. He struggles to speak \nand is frightened, but no one seems to care about him. \n3: A poor sailor was poisoned by some villains because he \nwon too much at dice. If he does not get an antidote he will \ndie. \n4: A merchant was robbed of a precious gold crown he \nhad bought for his daughter’s wedding. Without the crown,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Carry out every order of Hazir.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7FGUoXqISwEI3R41","name":"Fredrika Okland","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"dmrCAwwwUs9Yts3L","name":"Fredrika Okland - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fredrika Okland","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 205.","positive":"I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Fredrika Okland","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oUrf4tvSnU3S3VA9","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fredrika Okland","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me. \nAgenda: To heal my father and make him the good man who raised me.\nAleksander Okland</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 205.","owner":"Fredrika Okland","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-fredrika-okland-205","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":205,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me. \nAgenda: To heal my father and make him the good man who raised me.\nAleksander Okland</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To heal my father and make him the good man who raised me.\nAleksander Okland","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7bA6AM8NIgVcDWM0","name":"The Four Daughters of Hazir","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"JtS4J7rKW7rr6nJ4","name":"The Four Daughters of Hazir - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Four Daughters of Hazir","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","positive":"We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Four Daughters of Hazir","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YEaKXjMpqT64aZ89","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Four Daughters of Hazir","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","owner":"The Four Daughters of Hazir","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-four-daughters-of-hazir-163","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7jgelMet4eBmMlNL","name":"Ice Golem","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"L3gCXDtficWW04k7","name":"Ice Golem - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ice Golem","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218.","positive":"I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Ice Golem","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SaG01fRW4z4f5ebV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ice Golem","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator. \nInformation: Pernille is the only one who knows the \nmagic formula that opens the portal located in the small \nlake, leading to the house of Sinikka, the Finland Woman. A Hunter who understands magic can also activate the \nportal by studying the passage. If both of these options are \nimpractical, Hunters can ask Iselin for help.\nThreat – The Magic Lake Portal</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218.","owner":"Ice Golem","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ice-golem-218","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":218,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator. \nInformation: Pernille is the only one who knows the \nmagic formula that opens the portal located in the small \nlake, leading to the house of Sinikka, the Finland Woman. A Hunter who understands magic can also activate the \nportal by studying the passage. If both of these options are \nimpractical, Hunters can ask Iselin for help.\nThreat – The Magic Lake Portal</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8VA68S0ThBGzvLLq","name":"Hazir the Poor Merchant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"rtbZ2wlotRJqBKGQ","name":"Hazir the Poor Merchant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hazir the Poor Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","positive":"I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hazir the Poor Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Eage07NrdS0HqEHU","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hazir the Poor Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart. \nAgenda: Return to my old life, perhaps without punishing \nthe beggar, for I understand the reasons for his selfishness. \nThe Imposter</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","owner":"Hazir the Poor Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-hazir-the-poor-merchant-163","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart. \nAgenda: Return to my old life, perhaps without punishing \nthe beggar, for I understand the reasons for his selfishness. \nThe Imposter</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Return to my old life, perhaps without punishing \nthe beggar, for I understand the reasons for his selfishness. \nThe Imposter","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8iYfFojQvO0TpvNj","name":"Dark Waters","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"5WfrddevDIfCkK2x","name":"Dark Waters - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dark Waters","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108.","positive":"Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Dark Waters","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aExVvpK8unR04NE1","name":"Gift - The Frigid Embrace of Death","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dark Waters","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When a subject \nplunges into the Dark Waters, they are attacked by the \nwater, which will try to enter their nose and mouth. If the \nsubject fails the Defense Check, they suffer 1 Wound from \nthe cold and lack of oxygen and become stuck in the water, \nunable to move. A successful Defense Check is required to \nget free and return to the surface or to descend into the \nDungeon. Singing the lullaby that Pepe knows causes the \nwaters to recede for one hour, allowing safe access. \nThe Dungeon</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Dark Waters","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qBkw4D5RYmdN13wP","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dark Waters","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.\nGift - The Frigid Embrace of Death: When a subject \nplunges into the Dark Waters, they are attacked by the \nwater, which will try to enter their nose and mouth. If the \nsubject fails the Defense Check, they suffer 1 Wound from \nthe cold and lack of oxygen and become stuck in the water, \nunable to move. A successful Defense Check is required to \nget free and return to the surface or to descend into the \nDungeon. Singing the lullaby that Pepe knows causes the \nwaters to recede for one hour, allowing safe access. \nThe Dungeon\nDescriptor: A bare dungeon where the remains of six small \nbodies are huddled together. In the center of the room, a mass \nof plants, seabed debris, and animal bodies are formed into a \nheart that pulsates with malevolent energy.\nMorning, Afternoon, and Evening: The Mother’s \nHeart is the fulcrum that gives life to Blanca’s spirit and to \ndestroy it is to put an end to Mother Blanca de las Lágrimas.\nThe Mother’s Heart</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108.","owner":"Dark Waters","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-dark-waters-108","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":108,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.\nGift - The Frigid Embrace of Death: When a subject \nplunges into the Dark Waters, they are attacked by the \nwater, which will try to enter their nose and mouth. If the \nsubject fails the Defense Check, they suffer 1 Wound from \nthe cold and lack of oxygen and become stuck in the water, \nunable to move. A successful Defense Check is required to \nget free and return to the surface or to descend into the \nDungeon. Singing the lullaby that Pepe knows causes the \nwaters to recede for one hour, allowing safe access. \nThe Dungeon\nDescriptor: A bare dungeon where the remains of six small \nbodies are huddled together. In the center of the room, a mass \nof plants, seabed debris, and animal bodies are formed into a \nheart that pulsates with malevolent energy.\nMorning, Afternoon, and Evening: The Mother’s \nHeart is the fulcrum that gives life to Blanca’s spirit and to \ndestroy it is to put an end to Mother Blanca de las Lágrimas.\nThe Mother’s Heart</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8q8TLsIN8LcLgiu7","name":"Rotten Wreck","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"NKjueY9hC7c0EmMl","name":"Rotten Wreck - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rotten Wreck","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 189.","positive":"Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Rotten Wreck","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644069,"modifiedTime":1781557644069,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ioE4r54V94sGo9kz","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rotten Wreck","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight. \nGift - Splinters and Scrap: If a Defense Check fails, the \ntarget falls overboard and suffers 1 Wound, and the Storyteller gets 1 Wreck Token. When the number of Wreck \nTokens reaches 3, the ship collapses in on itself, burying \neverything inside.\nHidden among diary pages filled with uninteresting travel \nnotes are entries about the island.\nNote 1: Boyce followed the creature that destroyed his ship \nand discovered that its lair was east of the beach. \nNote 2: With a group of trusted sailors, Boyce headed to the \ncastle that towers in the center of the island in search of help. \nNote 3: The only survivor of the journey to the castle, Boyce \nwrites in shaky handwriting, asking God’s forgiveness for his \nsins and for the companions he had to leave behind to escape.\nNote 4: A knight in strange red armor roams the beach. Now \nlonely and desperate, Boyce decides to try his best to get his \nattention.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 189.","owner":"Rotten Wreck","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644069,"modifiedTime":1781557644069,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-rotten-wreck-189","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":189,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight. \nGift - Splinters and Scrap: If a Defense Check fails, the \ntarget falls overboard and suffers 1 Wound, and the Storyteller gets 1 Wreck Token. When the number of Wreck \nTokens reaches 3, the ship collapses in on itself, burying \neverything inside.\nHidden among diary pages filled with uninteresting travel \nnotes are entries about the island.\nNote 1: Boyce followed the creature that destroyed his ship \nand discovered that its lair was east of the beach. \nNote 2: With a group of trusted sailors, Boyce headed to the \ncastle that towers in the center of the island in search of help. \nNote 3: The only survivor of the journey to the castle, Boyce \nwrites in shaky handwriting, asking God’s forgiveness for his \nsins and for the companions he had to leave behind to escape.\nNote 4: A knight in strange red armor roams the beach. Now \nlonely and desperate, Boyce decides to try his best to get his \nattention.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644069,"modifiedTime":1781557644069,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9itcPUuDWXmC5Zdo","name":"Anselm Wagner","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"v80LFw5LRl5wZ90i","name":"Anselm Wagner - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anselm Wagner","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","positive":"I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Anselm Wagner","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mJQnH7EeA6smKpOm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anselm Wagner","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous. \nAgenda: Keep an eye out for potential problems for the city \nand maintain a clean appearance. \n•\nArmsmen of the City</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","owner":"Anselm Wagner","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-anselm-wagner-136","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":136,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous. \nAgenda: Keep an eye out for potential problems for the city \nand maintain a clean appearance. \n•\nArmsmen of the City</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep an eye out for potential problems for the city \nand maintain a clean appearance. \n•\nArmsmen of the City","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"A9ctUKJhYEILk7NE","name":"Baba the Poor Conman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ENRkaAj87EniKVZ6","name":"Baba the Poor Conman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Baba the Poor Conman","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 161.","positive":"I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Baba the Poor Conman","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WAHwE7TwejNsdXVQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Baba the Poor Conman","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.\nAgenda: Use others to eliminate the remaining thieves and \nkeep the treasure all to myself.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 161.","owner":"Baba the Poor Conman","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-baba-the-poor-conman-161","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":161,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.\nAgenda: Use others to eliminate the remaining thieves and \nkeep the treasure all to myself.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Use others to eliminate the remaining thieves and \nkeep the treasure all to myself.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"AXQ4KJucw2vLFoCG","name":"The Alchemical Door","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"XB0otUapXecZos8j","name":"The Alchemical Door - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Alchemical Door","source":"Rome, City of the Order","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 66.","positive":"A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Alchemical Door","source":"Rome, City of the Order","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638382,"modifiedTime":1781557638382,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WqM7lIKDah1AcmPY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Alchemical Door","source":"Rome, City of the Order","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door. \nGift - Magic Door: No Gift, magic, or effect can open the \ndoor, for the engraved seal draws its power directly from \nthe soul of the One Who Plots in the Shadows. The only \nway to open the door is to say the magical words A Fairytale Turned Upside Down . It is possible, however, to pass \npapers and envelopes under the doorframe, and this is how \nSilvan keeps his master informed of his discoveries. \nIf Silvan is present: The guide will tell you that the \nprevious owner of the villa was an eccentric Baron who \ndecided to live in a tree. Many say that the Baron’s ghost \nstill roams the streets of Rome, appearing some nights to \nfrighten passersby. The villa was bought for little money \nby a strange figure whose name no one remembers. The \nstranger came from the north, but after the purchase, he \ndid not spend a single night in the house.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 66.","owner":"The Alchemical Door","source":"Rome, City of the Order","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638382,"modifiedTime":1781557638382,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-rome-city-of-the-order-the-alchemical-door-66","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"rome-city-of-the-order","adventureTitle":"Rome, City of the Order","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":66,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Rome, City of the Order","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door. \nGift - Magic Door: No Gift, magic, or effect can open the \ndoor, for the engraved seal draws its power directly from \nthe soul of the One Who Plots in the Shadows. The only \nway to open the door is to say the magical words A Fairytale Turned Upside Down . It is possible, however, to pass \npapers and envelopes under the doorframe, and this is how \nSilvan keeps his master informed of his discoveries. \nIf Silvan is present: The guide will tell you that the \nprevious owner of the villa was an eccentric Baron who \ndecided to live in a tree. Many say that the Baron’s ghost \nstill roams the streets of Rome, appearing some nights to \nfrighten passersby. The villa was bought for little money \nby a strange figure whose name no one remembers. The \nstranger came from the north, but after the purchase, he \ndid not spend a single night in the house.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638382,"modifiedTime":1781557638382,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BliQMnFyozVnGJIS","name":"The Merchant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"rjNNbXXEFgYlWa8T","name":"The Merchant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 152.","positive":"I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642142,"modifiedTime":1781557642142,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c5i9oJsf9TQbnBcB","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself. \nAgenda: Escape the island by secretly boarding a ship, or \nfind a way to appease the Djinn’s wrath.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 152.","owner":"The Merchant","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642143,"modifiedTime":1781557642143,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-merchant-152","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":152,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself. \nAgenda: Escape the island by secretly boarding a ship, or \nfind a way to appease the Djinn’s wrath.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escape the island by secretly boarding a ship, or \nfind a way to appease the Djinn’s wrath.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642143,"modifiedTime":1781557642143,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CQxQ77TVe0URL7Xc","name":"Ice Layer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"uwwQ6oynwf9OQUPJ","name":"Ice Layer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ice Layer","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 220.","positive":"A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Ice Layer","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645745,"modifiedTime":1781557645745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h8CnjJ6t6swVnah3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ice Layer","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms. \nInformation: Exploration of the castle is handled by \nEncounter Rooms, each with a different challenge for the \nHunters. These places represent the will of the Ice Heart \nto eliminate unwanted guests. After each Encounter Room, \nthe Hunters will wander through other neutral rooms, \nwhere they will find information about Lady Storm, the \ntrue owner of the castle. These rooms are important because they provide vital clues as to what kind of heat can \nscratch the Ice Heart, as explained on page 224.\n1\n2</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 220.","owner":"Ice Layer","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645745,"modifiedTime":1781557645745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ice-layer-220","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":220,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms. \nInformation: Exploration of the castle is handled by \nEncounter Rooms, each with a different challenge for the \nHunters. These places represent the will of the Ice Heart \nto eliminate unwanted guests. After each Encounter Room, \nthe Hunters will wander through other neutral rooms, \nwhere they will find information about Lady Storm, the \ntrue owner of the castle. These rooms are important because they provide vital clues as to what kind of heat can \nscratch the Ice Heart, as explained on page 224.\n1\n2</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645745,"modifiedTime":1781557645745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CSi3PSgrooXAP9l5","name":"Demonic Dogs","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"h2cafWw1SeG4rvrS","name":"Demonic Dogs - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Demonic Dogs","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 143.","positive":"We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Demonic Dogs","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jHHdK39wJomzekUu","name":"Gift - Demonic Powers","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Demonic Dogs","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>These creatures can fly, with \nall the narrative benefits that brings. As supernatural creatures, Demonic Dogs are immune to all effects of fear and \nmind manipulation. Those who use magic against them \ntake 1 Penalty to all related Checks and must pay 1 additional Soma if it is required to activate magic. A Demonic Dog \ncan spend 1 Reset Token to increase its OL to Hard 7 for a \nsingle action, but not to defend itself.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 143.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Demonic Dogs","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DK7xDqSNN3D5Xu9B","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Demonic Dogs","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC \n(2 Wounds - 3 Dogs)\nDescriptor: We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey. \nAgenda: To kill as many humans as possible and thereby \nincrease our power. \nGift - Demonic Powers: These creatures can fly, with \nall the narrative benefits that brings. As supernatural creatures, Demonic Dogs are immune to all effects of fear and \nmind manipulation. Those who use magic against them \ntake 1 Penalty to all related Checks and must pay 1 additional Soma if it is required to activate magic. A Demonic Dog \ncan spend 1 Reset Token to increase its OL to Hard 7 for a \nsingle action, but not to defend itself. \nInformation: When the Demonic Dogs are defeated, \nBritta or a witch who has read her diary can place a magical seal on the Magic Tinderbox: \nthe object will lose some of \nits power and become the \nTreasure of the Order, \nThe Tinderbox of Second Chances (see page \n28). \nScenario Gifts\nThese Gifts represent special abilities related to The Last \nWish Scenario and can be acquired once conditions are \nmet. A Hunter can acquire one Scenario Gift. If they acquire a new one during an Interlude, they will have to forgo \nthe previous one.\nDéjà vu \nRequirement: Witness the effect of one or more Resets.\nBy experiencing temporal shifts, you are able to notice the \nsmall differences in the fabric of reality. Once per Scene, \nyou can spend 1 Soma to activate each of the following effects:\n1. I’ve Already Got It: Y ou already have an item that belongs to the Place you are in, and if it is a unique item, no \none has noticed that it is missing.\n2. I Was Already Here: Y ou can move to any Place you \ncan see from where you are without anyone being able to \nstop you; to the eyes of anyone present, it will look as if you \nhave always been where you are now.\n3. I’ve Seen It Before: The Storyteller will reveal the \neffect of a particular Gift or equipment from an NPC in \nfront of you that you must have known or met before.\nNote: This Gift can only be used when the use of a \nspell that affects the normal flow of time is manifested, like a Reset. Outside of this Scenario, it is up \nto the Storyteller to determine if the Hunter can use \nthis Gift again.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 143.","owner":"Demonic Dogs","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-demonic-dogs-143","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":143,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC \n(2 Wounds - 3 Dogs)\nDescriptor: We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey. \nAgenda: To kill as many humans as possible and thereby \nincrease our power. \nGift - Demonic Powers: These creatures can fly, with \nall the narrative benefits that brings. As supernatural creatures, Demonic Dogs are immune to all effects of fear and \nmind manipulation. Those who use magic against them \ntake 1 Penalty to all related Checks and must pay 1 additional Soma if it is required to activate magic. A Demonic Dog \ncan spend 1 Reset Token to increase its OL to Hard 7 for a \nsingle action, but not to defend itself. \nInformation: When the Demonic Dogs are defeated, \nBritta or a witch who has read her diary can place a magical seal on the Magic Tinderbox: \nthe object will lose some of \nits power and become the \nTreasure of the Order, \nThe Tinderbox of Second Chances (see page \n28). \nScenario Gifts\nThese Gifts represent special abilities related to The Last \nWish Scenario and can be acquired once conditions are \nmet. A Hunter can acquire one Scenario Gift. If they acquire a new one during an Interlude, they will have to forgo \nthe previous one.\nDéjà vu \nRequirement: Witness the effect of one or more Resets.\nBy experiencing temporal shifts, you are able to notice the \nsmall differences in the fabric of reality. Once per Scene, \nyou can spend 1 Soma to activate each of the following effects:\n1. I’ve Already Got It: Y ou already have an item that belongs to the Place you are in, and if it is a unique item, no \none has noticed that it is missing.\n2. I Was Already Here: Y ou can move to any Place you \ncan see from where you are without anyone being able to \nstop you; to the eyes of anyone present, it will look as if you \nhave always been where you are now.\n3. I’ve Seen It Before: The Storyteller will reveal the \neffect of a particular Gift or equipment from an NPC in \nfront of you that you must have known or met before.\nNote: This Gift can only be used when the use of a \nspell that affects the normal flow of time is manifested, like a Reset. Outside of this Scenario, it is up \nto the Storyteller to determine if the Hunter can use \nthis Gift again.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To kill as many humans as possible and thereby \nincrease our power.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CUdwz0SJFHONcmNS","name":"Father Neron Lobo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"GPJdvt68Ejxe9LEX","name":"Father Neron Lobo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Neron Lobo","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 102.","positive":"I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Father Neron Lobo","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639852,"modifiedTime":1781557639852,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fcYFuMdE0rpiZuOV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Neron Lobo","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person. \nAgenda: Save the children of Murcia from the threat of the \nMadre Blanca de las Lágrimas. \nGift - Exorcist Priest: Father Neron has the ability to \nperceive damned souls, which allows him to see and inter-act with all spiritual creatures. He can perform an exorcism \nand inflict 1 Wound on a target with the word Spirit in its \nprofile. No Defense Check can be made against this attack.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 102.","owner":"Father Neron Lobo","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639852,"modifiedTime":1781557639852,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-father-neron-lobo-102","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":102,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person. \nAgenda: Save the children of Murcia from the threat of the \nMadre Blanca de las Lágrimas. \nGift - Exorcist Priest: Father Neron has the ability to \nperceive damned souls, which allows him to see and inter-act with all spiritual creatures. He can perform an exorcism \nand inflict 1 Wound on a target with the word Spirit in its \nprofile. No Defense Check can be made against this attack.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Save the children of Murcia from the threat of the \nMadre Blanca de las Lágrimas.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639852,"modifiedTime":1781557639852,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DN0U23LnG3Wj9k9M","name":"City Chaos","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"1zdqs6gs3rDBLpUS","name":"City Chaos - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"City Chaos","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 99.","positive":"Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"City Chaos","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639711,"modifiedTime":1781557639711,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iHxeNYqVmn02HYyA","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"City Chaos","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people. \nGift - Time Waste: By Failing a Check against this \nThreat, the Hunters fall victim to the city’s confusion and \ntheir trip takes longer than planned, so they arrive at a later time slot. A Positive Outcome means the Hunters arrive \nat their goal destination one time slot after their departure \n(e.g., leave in the Morning and arrive in the Afternoon). A \nFailed Check delays the Hunter’s arrival by one time slot, so \nthat their journey takes two periods of the day (e.g., leave \nin the Morning, arrive in the Evening). Failing the Check, \nhowever, allows the Hunters to learn one of the rumors circulating in the city. The Storyteller rolls a die or can choose \nwhich rumor reaches the Hunters’ ears:\n1: The Bats are a gang of street urchins who regularly steal \nfrom the city’s merchants. The seven brats who make up \nthe gang live in the old Clock Tower, and though many residents turn a blind eye to their misdeeds, it seems that some \nnobles are planning to raid the Tower and put an \nend to the gang. \n2: A new priest has recently arrived in the \ncity, but he does not seem to have taken up his \nministry in any of the churches open to the \nfaithful. The stranger is a burly, rude-looking \nfellow who lives in an old Monastery that no \none has used in decades.\n3: A dark rumor describes a ghost that \nhaunts Murcia during November. Parents \nmust be very careful with their children \nbecause the Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas \nwanders among the living in the guise of a</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 99.","owner":"City Chaos","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639711,"modifiedTime":1781557639711,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-city-chaos-99","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":99,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people. \nGift - Time Waste: By Failing a Check against this \nThreat, the Hunters fall victim to the city’s confusion and \ntheir trip takes longer than planned, so they arrive at a later time slot. A Positive Outcome means the Hunters arrive \nat their goal destination one time slot after their departure \n(e.g., leave in the Morning and arrive in the Afternoon). A \nFailed Check delays the Hunter’s arrival by one time slot, so \nthat their journey takes two periods of the day (e.g., leave \nin the Morning, arrive in the Evening). Failing the Check, \nhowever, allows the Hunters to learn one of the rumors circulating in the city. The Storyteller rolls a die or can choose \nwhich rumor reaches the Hunters’ ears:\n1: The Bats are a gang of street urchins who regularly steal \nfrom the city’s merchants. The seven brats who make up \nthe gang live in the old Clock Tower, and though many residents turn a blind eye to their misdeeds, it seems that some \nnobles are planning to raid the Tower and put an \nend to the gang. \n2: A new priest has recently arrived in the \ncity, but he does not seem to have taken up his \nministry in any of the churches open to the \nfaithful. The stranger is a burly, rude-looking \nfellow who lives in an old Monastery that no \none has used in decades.\n3: A dark rumor describes a ghost that \nhaunts Murcia during November. Parents \nmust be very careful with their children \nbecause the Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas \nwanders among the living in the guise of a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639711,"modifiedTime":1781557639711,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DmOmEJScBxcNf3Ba","name":"Nikola’s Bats","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Y1IrHBDYFqk3NfYt","name":"Nikola’s Bats - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nikola’s Bats","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 126.","positive":"We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Nikola’s Bats","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640775,"modifiedTime":1781557640775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QJI7HkLIPvBQrCem","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nikola’s Bats","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder. \nAgenda: Protect Nikola while he sleeps.\nGift - Swarm: Bats are considered a single unit with 5 Wounds. \nAny damage dealt reduces the total by 1, and attacks that hit an \narea inflict 1 additional Wound. As a swarm, Nikola’s Bats can \nbite up to 3 different targets in a single action. The flapping \nof the Bats’ wings causes discomfort to living creatures: \nas the swarm rises, each Hunter present loses 2 Soma, \nwhile NPCs suffer 1 Wound from fatigue.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 126.","owner":"Nikola’s Bats","source":"Nikola's Pledge","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640775,"modifiedTime":1781557640775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-nikola-s-bats-126","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":126,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder. \nAgenda: Protect Nikola while he sleeps.\nGift - Swarm: Bats are considered a single unit with 5 Wounds. \nAny damage dealt reduces the total by 1, and attacks that hit an \narea inflict 1 additional Wound. As a swarm, Nikola’s Bats can \nbite up to 3 different targets in a single action. The flapping \nof the Bats’ wings causes discomfort to living creatures: \nas the swarm rises, each Hunter present loses 2 Soma, \nwhile NPCs suffer 1 Wound from fatigue.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":5},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect Nikola while he sleeps.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640775,"modifiedTime":1781557640775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EqmrHgu42Me1etMj","name":"Uther Pendragon","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"8SDPdxLDataQTT8x","name":"Uther Pendragon - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Uther Pendragon","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 194.","positive":"I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Uther Pendragon","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644240,"modifiedTime":1781557644240,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HO4Hw799LElPFXtX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Uther Pendragon","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (0 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.\nAgenda: Protect Camelot and bring Arthur to his senses so \nthat he can once again be a worthy ruler of these lands. \nInformation: Uther is dying, and even if he is saved, it \nwill be clear that his injuries are fatal. Before he breathes \nhis last, however, the old man will reveal important details \nto the Hunters.\n ◆ Arthur was always a good ruler, as long as Merlin remained at his side as an advisor. Uther, however, could \nalways see envy in the Sorcerer’s eyes, envy for the \nyoung king that was his protégé. When Merlin suddenly disappeared, Arthur went mad and lost all the traits \nthat made him a righteous and benevolent man.\n ◆ In the southeast, past the great Lake, lies an old Abandoned House. Arthur spent his childhood there, and \nUther is convinced that the spirit of all that is good in \nhis son’s heart dwells there.\n ◆ There is a secret passage to enter the Camelot Castle. It \nis located inside a large oak tree that has been struck by \nlightning. From there, an underground tunnel leads to \nthe hall of the Round Table. \nZone 8 – Camelot Castle\nDescription: Camelot Castle appears to be an ancient \nabandoned ruin, with only the cackling of soldiers preparing for war revealing that it is still inhabited. Knights and \nvillagers alike are busy crafting weapons and war machines. \nInformation: Arthur is in the hall of the Round Table, \nwhere he sits with his most trusted Knights. There are thirteen seats in total, one is occupied by Arthur, and one is \nempty as it belongs to Merlin. There are then eleven more \nKnights (page 181), but for every Empty Seat Token that \nthe Hunters have collected, the number is reduced by one. \nWithout his Virtues, Arthur is an invading madman whose \ngoal is the conquest of Europe, second only to finding his \nbeloved Guinevere. Arthur’s behavior is greatly influenced \nby finding the Virtue of Wisdom (page 194).</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 194.","owner":"Uther Pendragon","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644240,"modifiedTime":1781557644240,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-uther-pendragon-194","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":194,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (0 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.\nAgenda: Protect Camelot and bring Arthur to his senses so \nthat he can once again be a worthy ruler of these lands. \nInformation: Uther is dying, and even if he is saved, it \nwill be clear that his injuries are fatal. Before he breathes \nhis last, however, the old man will reveal important details \nto the Hunters.\n ◆ Arthur was always a good ruler, as long as Merlin remained at his side as an advisor. Uther, however, could \nalways see envy in the Sorcerer’s eyes, envy for the \nyoung king that was his protégé. When Merlin suddenly disappeared, Arthur went mad and lost all the traits \nthat made him a righteous and benevolent man.\n ◆ In the southeast, past the great Lake, lies an old Abandoned House. Arthur spent his childhood there, and \nUther is convinced that the spirit of all that is good in \nhis son’s heart dwells there.\n ◆ There is a secret passage to enter the Camelot Castle. It \nis located inside a large oak tree that has been struck by \nlightning. From there, an underground tunnel leads to \nthe hall of the Round Table. \nZone 8 – Camelot Castle\nDescription: Camelot Castle appears to be an ancient \nabandoned ruin, with only the cackling of soldiers preparing for war revealing that it is still inhabited. Knights and \nvillagers alike are busy crafting weapons and war machines. \nInformation: Arthur is in the hall of the Round Table, \nwhere he sits with his most trusted Knights. There are thirteen seats in total, one is occupied by Arthur, and one is \nempty as it belongs to Merlin. There are then eleven more \nKnights (page 181), but for every Empty Seat Token that \nthe Hunters have collected, the number is reduced by one. \nWithout his Virtues, Arthur is an invading madman whose \ngoal is the conquest of Europe, second only to finding his \nbeloved Guinevere. Arthur’s behavior is greatly influenced \nby finding the Virtue of Wisdom (page 194).</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":0},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect Camelot and bring Arthur to his senses so \nthat he can once again be a worthy ruler of these lands.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644240,"modifiedTime":1781557644240,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FdPWtUCbcwUe2XWL","name":"Ice Soldier","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"6twiKN1X9kVn9TUC","name":"Ice Soldier - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ice Soldier","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 222.","positive":"I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Ice Soldier","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zFMjlZvTK9zqqxzL","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ice Soldier","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people. \nInformation: The trapped people are mostly treasure \nseekers, but if you look closely, you can see some of the \nBergen nobles. It will be clear to the Hunters that the sick \npeople who made it to the castle are trapped inside the columns. The columns are difficult to melt, and the people \ninside them are dead. Approaching a column without an \noccupant will activate Threat - Columns of Eternal Sleep.\n Threat – Columns of Eternal Sleep</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 222.","owner":"Ice Soldier","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ice-soldier-222","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":222,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people. \nInformation: The trapped people are mostly treasure \nseekers, but if you look closely, you can see some of the \nBergen nobles. It will be clear to the Hunters that the sick \npeople who made it to the castle are trapped inside the columns. The columns are difficult to melt, and the people \ninside them are dead. Approaching a column without an \noccupant will activate Threat - Columns of Eternal Sleep.\n Threat – Columns of Eternal Sleep</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FhyUF3wGPgFm5zf9","name":"Britta the Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ytqyiadAK6OkGYZz","name":"Britta the Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Britta the Witch","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142.","positive":"I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Britta the Witch","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2igh5qdNbHeFzfBu","name":"Gift - Britta’s Witchcraft","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Britta the Witch","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Britta can perform various \nrituals to achieve different effects: she can find someone or \nsomething, she can change the weather in the area, or she \ncan communicate with and take control of an animal. All of \nthese rituals take about ten minutes to complete. Britta can \nalso dispel magic, a practice in which she is a true master. \nIn a single action, Britta can end a spell or block the power \nof a Treasure of the Order until the end of the Scene.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Britta the Witch","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8xmKR6NcCYFV4Sw3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Britta the Witch","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.\nAgenda: Stop the power of the Magic Tinderbox before the \nDemonic Dogs inside it become too powerful. \nGift - Britta’s Witchcraft: Britta can perform various \nrituals to achieve different effects: she can find someone or \nsomething, she can change the weather in the area, or she \ncan communicate with and take control of an animal. All of \nthese rituals take about ten minutes to complete. Britta can \nalso dispel magic, a practice in which she is a true master. \nIn a single action, Britta can end a spell or block the power \nof a Treasure of the Order until the end of the Scene. \nInformation: Britta will tell the Hunters the secret of the \nMagic Tinderbox and that she can use her magic to stop the \ndisasters Bastian is causing, but there is a catch. Once the \nMagic Tinderbox’s power is blocked, the three Demonic \nDogs inside will be released and must be defeated to send \nthem back into the magical object.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142.","owner":"Britta the Witch","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-britta-the-witch-142","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":142,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.\nAgenda: Stop the power of the Magic Tinderbox before the \nDemonic Dogs inside it become too powerful. \nGift - Britta’s Witchcraft: Britta can perform various \nrituals to achieve different effects: she can find someone or \nsomething, she can change the weather in the area, or she \ncan communicate with and take control of an animal. All of \nthese rituals take about ten minutes to complete. Britta can \nalso dispel magic, a practice in which she is a true master. \nIn a single action, Britta can end a spell or block the power \nof a Treasure of the Order until the end of the Scene. \nInformation: Britta will tell the Hunters the secret of the \nMagic Tinderbox and that she can use her magic to stop the \ndisasters Bastian is causing, but there is a catch. Once the \nMagic Tinderbox’s power is blocked, the three Demonic \nDogs inside will be released and must be defeated to send \nthem back into the magical object.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Stop the power of the Magic Tinderbox before the \nDemonic Dogs inside it become too powerful.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FmCI0DPoPWEDpot9","name":"Ravn","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"rJPjmL0QhT3DnXv0","name":"Ravn - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ravn","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210.","positive":"I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Ravn","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4AD4D3qKoKTgQx3P","name":"Gift - The Raven","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ravn","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, Ravn can transform \ninto a raven and escape by flying away. If he makes a sur -\nprise attack, Ravn inflicts 1 Additional Wound.\nKråke</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ravn","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xGPy1eZd7s9PZHlX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ravn","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness. \nAgenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business. \nGift - The Raven: Once per Scene, Ravn can transform \ninto a raven and escape by flying away. If he makes a sur -\nprise attack, Ravn inflicts 1 Additional Wound.\nKråke</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210.","owner":"Ravn","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ravn-210","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":210,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness. \nAgenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business. \nGift - The Raven: Once per Scene, Ravn can transform \ninto a raven and escape by flying away. If he makes a sur -\nprise attack, Ravn inflicts 1 Additional Wound.\nKråke</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FmoeOJTuXpMjnwHN","name":"Sister Esperanza","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"J0Iv9GU3ErLBKhC4","name":"Sister Esperanza - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sister Esperanza","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 107.","positive":"I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Sister Esperanza","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Cm1oSaFsYsVAeq9V","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sister Esperanza","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent. \nAgenda: Helping Father Neron and taking care of the children in the Monastery.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 107.","owner":"Sister Esperanza","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-sister-esperanza-107","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":107,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent. \nAgenda: Helping Father Neron and taking care of the children in the Monastery.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Helping Father Neron and taking care of the children in the Monastery.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GDn0zbg4p4WkoayP","name":"Miss Snow","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"vuGZ06Efp04frOJi","name":"Miss Snow - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Miss Snow","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 227.","positive":"I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Miss Snow","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646296,"modifiedTime":1781557646296,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JE0zqoTVrJstiuAh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Miss Snow","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others. \n \nGift – Snow Sorceress Apprentice: Miss Snow can use the Gifts of the \nSnow Sorceress and Winter’s Kiss, but when she does, she rolls a die, and \nif she rolls a 4 or higher, a magical disaster (determined by the Storyteller) \noccurs, complicating the situation.\nDescriptors and Gifts\nI am a powerful ice sorceress and can manipulate the weather. I want \nSnow to learn to be a Hunter, so I limit the use of my powers to solving \nproblems for her. \n• Snow Sorceress: Y ou can use magic to create and manipulate the cold. \nDescribe the effects of a spell that has one of the following Keywords as a condition: Ice, Snow, or Frost. Y ou could, for example, Create an Ice Bridge \nto cross a crevasse or Freeze an Enemy to immobilize it. Pay a cost of 1 to 2 \nSoma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate the spell. The effects you describe \nlast until the end of the Scene. The Soma cost is increased by 1 when environmental conditions are not compatible with cold.\nI am impassive and know how to assert my authority, nothing can \nshake my heart. I have a weakness for those who show true love or \nfriendship, and it comes naturally to me to help these people, although \nI do not want anyone to notice this weakness of mine. \n• Winter’s Kiss: In you lies the power of winter. When you give someone \na chaste kiss, you can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Erase one of their memories. It must be the memory of an event in the Scene \nin which you use this effect. Particularly capable Hunters and NPCs may require a Position Check for the effect to succeed.\n2. Make the subject immune to cold for the rest of the Scene. This will prevent \nthem from suffering Wounds from frost and make them immune to the effects \nof the Snow Sorceress Gift. \n3. Make an object extremely fragile. \nY ou can spend 1 Soma when you use this Gift to blow a kiss to the target, thus \navoiding physical contact.\nI have a special insight into understanding people and their intentions, \nand with my magic, I can quickly create help for the weak. I dislike people who talk too much and social events. \n• Dark Ego - Deus Ex Machina: When all seems lost, use your magic \nto make truth triumph. Reduce by 1 the Soma cost of spells you cast with \nthe Gift of the Snow Sorceress when your goal is to help someone. Once per \nExchange, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent one of your allies from taking \n1 Wound by protecting them with a wall of icy frost. Y ou can use the Gift of \nWinter’s Kiss as a free action once per Exchange.\nActivator: Step in and show your power to save a good-hearted person from the \ndanger that threatens them.\nEquipment\nA brooch in the shape of a sleigh / A small knife with an ice blade that never \nmelts / A scarf handmade by Miss Snow / Books of magic / A mirror fragment \nwith a strange magical aura.\nSoma\n 5\nPX\nLady Storm and \nMiss Snow\nIam a powerful witch who rules over winter and frost. Because of a betrayal, I was robbed of my \nbody for a long time and a new personality was created in me: Miss Snow. As much as I hate to admit \nit, it is thanks to Miss Snow that I have regained my full strength, and I intend to help her find her way. Thanks to my magic, I have given her a body, and now we are like twins: identical in appearance, \nbut profoundly different in character. Snow has agreed to remain in the ranks of the Order, and until she is able to fend for herself, I will watch over her. \nSpecial: Miss Snow is an NPC under the complete control of the Storyteller. Lady Storm guards over her on her missions on behalf of the Order. \nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nAdditional \nWound.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 227.","owner":"Miss Snow","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646296,"modifiedTime":1781557646296,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-miss-snow-227","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":227,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>- (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others. \n \nGift – Snow Sorceress Apprentice: Miss Snow can use the Gifts of the \nSnow Sorceress and Winter’s Kiss, but when she does, she rolls a die, and \nif she rolls a 4 or higher, a magical disaster (determined by the Storyteller) \noccurs, complicating the situation.\nDescriptors and Gifts\nI am a powerful ice sorceress and can manipulate the weather. I want \nSnow to learn to be a Hunter, so I limit the use of my powers to solving \nproblems for her. \n• Snow Sorceress: Y ou can use magic to create and manipulate the cold. \nDescribe the effects of a spell that has one of the following Keywords as a condition: Ice, Snow, or Frost. Y ou could, for example, Create an Ice Bridge \nto cross a crevasse or Freeze an Enemy to immobilize it. Pay a cost of 1 to 2 \nSoma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate the spell. The effects you describe \nlast until the end of the Scene. The Soma cost is increased by 1 when environmental conditions are not compatible with cold.\nI am impassive and know how to assert my authority, nothing can \nshake my heart. I have a weakness for those who show true love or \nfriendship, and it comes naturally to me to help these people, although \nI do not want anyone to notice this weakness of mine. \n• Winter’s Kiss: In you lies the power of winter. When you give someone \na chaste kiss, you can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Erase one of their memories. It must be the memory of an event in the Scene \nin which you use this effect. Particularly capable Hunters and NPCs may require a Position Check for the effect to succeed.\n2. Make the subject immune to cold for the rest of the Scene. This will prevent \nthem from suffering Wounds from frost and make them immune to the effects \nof the Snow Sorceress Gift. \n3. Make an object extremely fragile. \nY ou can spend 1 Soma when you use this Gift to blow a kiss to the target, thus \navoiding physical contact.\nI have a special insight into understanding people and their intentions, \nand with my magic, I can quickly create help for the weak. I dislike people who talk too much and social events. \n• Dark Ego - Deus Ex Machina: When all seems lost, use your magic \nto make truth triumph. Reduce by 1 the Soma cost of spells you cast with \nthe Gift of the Snow Sorceress when your goal is to help someone. Once per \nExchange, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent one of your allies from taking \n1 Wound by protecting them with a wall of icy frost. Y ou can use the Gift of \nWinter’s Kiss as a free action once per Exchange.\nActivator: Step in and show your power to save a good-hearted person from the \ndanger that threatens them.\nEquipment\nA brooch in the shape of a sleigh / A small knife with an ice blade that never \nmelts / A scarf handmade by Miss Snow / Books of magic / A mirror fragment \nwith a strange magical aura.\nSoma\n 5\nPX\nLady Storm and \nMiss Snow\nIam a powerful witch who rules over winter and frost. Because of a betrayal, I was robbed of my \nbody for a long time and a new personality was created in me: Miss Snow. As much as I hate to admit \nit, it is thanks to Miss Snow that I have regained my full strength, and I intend to help her find her way. Thanks to my magic, I have given her a body, and now we are like twins: identical in appearance, \nbut profoundly different in character. Snow has agreed to remain in the ranks of the Order, and until she is able to fend for herself, I will watch over her. \nSpecial: Miss Snow is an NPC under the complete control of the Storyteller. Lady Storm guards over her on her missions on behalf of the Order. \nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nAdditional \nWound.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646296,"modifiedTime":1781557646296,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GEI9e3XyOywYFwlb","name":"Survivors of the First Expedition","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jCSOXotmOD9epzTD","name":"Survivors of the First Expedition - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Survivors of the First Expedition","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 181.","positive":"We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Survivors of the First Expedition","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"f4k72lOIeDZwjyIT","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Survivors of the First Expedition","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.\nAgenda: To be able to escape from this cursed island.\nInformation: At each encounter, 1d6 Survivors will be \navailable to talk about an adjacent Zone from which they \nare fleeing. The Storyteller decides what information the \nSurvivors have. When talking about the previous expedition, the Survivors will tell you that as soon as they docked \non the beach (Zone 2 - Beach page 188), the ship was attacked by a huge creature that they describe as a collection \nof different animals. The crew fled in all directions, scattering across the island as the ship was destroyed. Captain \nBoyce, who was in command of the ship, heroically stayed \nbehind to wrestle with the creature so that everyone could \nescape.\nSaxon Marauders</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 181.","owner":"Survivors of the First Expedition","source":"The King's Awakening","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-survivors-of-the-first-expedition-181","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":181,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.\nAgenda: To be able to escape from this cursed island.\nInformation: At each encounter, 1d6 Survivors will be \navailable to talk about an adjacent Zone from which they \nare fleeing. The Storyteller decides what information the \nSurvivors have. When talking about the previous expedition, the Survivors will tell you that as soon as they docked \non the beach (Zone 2 - Beach page 188), the ship was attacked by a huge creature that they describe as a collection \nof different animals. The crew fled in all directions, scattering across the island as the ship was destroyed. Captain \nBoyce, who was in command of the ship, heroically stayed \nbehind to wrestle with the creature so that everyone could \nescape.\nSaxon Marauders</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To be able to escape from this cursed island.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GSZV0gIfXbhRN4HJ","name":"Hugo the Potter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"djoM3goMAxauxIpB","name":"Hugo the Potter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hugo the Potter","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 135.","positive":"I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hugo the Potter","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641396,"modifiedTime":1781557641396,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aHjt3cnOA0v1Ja5R","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hugo the Potter","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers. \nInformation: As the first Place that Bastian will use the \nMagic Tinderbox to escape the Hunters, this is where the \nHunters will start again after each Reset. Unlike normal humans, the Hunters will retain a memory of what happened \nat each Reset.\nFirst Reset: The Hunters will notice that some powerful \nmagic has taken effect, and time seems to have rewound \nto a few minutes before they meet Bastian. The deserter is \nabsent, but Hugo the Potter is behind his stall, smiling at \npassersby. The Black Cat walks between the legs of one of \nthe Hunters, stops to watch them with intelligent eyes, and \nthen walks away. \nSecond Reset: Same as the First Reset, except the Cat \nwill stop with the Hunters and try to get them to follow her, \nleading them to Britta’s house.\nThird Reset: Like the First Reset, but this time the Hunters will find Anselm Wagner waiting for them with an \nescort of ten gendarmes. The nobleman will tell the Hunters that he has received a report from a trusted man about \ntheir impending arrival in the city. The nobleman has made \nno request of the Order and wants no trouble, so he will \nask the Hunters to leave. It will be clear that Anselm has</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 135.","owner":"Hugo the Potter","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641396,"modifiedTime":1781557641396,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-hugo-the-potter-135","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":135,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers. \nInformation: As the first Place that Bastian will use the \nMagic Tinderbox to escape the Hunters, this is where the \nHunters will start again after each Reset. Unlike normal humans, the Hunters will retain a memory of what happened \nat each Reset.\nFirst Reset: The Hunters will notice that some powerful \nmagic has taken effect, and time seems to have rewound \nto a few minutes before they meet Bastian. The deserter is \nabsent, but Hugo the Potter is behind his stall, smiling at \npassersby. The Black Cat walks between the legs of one of \nthe Hunters, stops to watch them with intelligent eyes, and \nthen walks away. \nSecond Reset: Same as the First Reset, except the Cat \nwill stop with the Hunters and try to get them to follow her, \nleading them to Britta’s house.\nThird Reset: Like the First Reset, but this time the Hunters will find Anselm Wagner waiting for them with an \nescort of ten gendarmes. The nobleman will tell the Hunters that he has received a report from a trusted man about \ntheir impending arrival in the city. The nobleman has made \nno request of the Order and wants no trouble, so he will \nask the Hunters to leave. It will be clear that Anselm has</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641396,"modifiedTime":1781557641396,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"H7UrhFvFlFsLPLCH","name":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"MMiNjpDATJggpGHt","name":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 103.","positive":"I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639868,"modifiedTime":1781557639868,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GJgqdMRiT7b3kvOa","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace. \nAgenda: I will bring seven children into the water. They will become \nmy children.\nGift - Spirit of Tears: Blanca’s body does not follow the laws of life \nand death, and until her heart is at peace, she cannot be permanently eliminated. When Blanca’s Wounds are all marked, she crumbles \nto dust and her spirit returns to Blanca’s House, summoned by the \nMother’s Heart (page 107). At the beginning of the next Scene, Blanca heals all her Wounds. She starts each Scene as Intangible . If she \nacts to harm a living subject (inflicting 1 Wound, grabbing them, and \nsimilar actions), she becomes Tangible for the rest of the Scene. Once \nper Scene, Blanca can choose to become Intangible again.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 103.","owner":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas","source":"A Mother's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639868,"modifiedTime":1781557639868,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-madre-blanca-de-las-l-grimas-103","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":103,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace. \nAgenda: I will bring seven children into the water. They will become \nmy children.\nGift - Spirit of Tears: Blanca’s body does not follow the laws of life \nand death, and until her heart is at peace, she cannot be permanently eliminated. When Blanca’s Wounds are all marked, she crumbles \nto dust and her spirit returns to Blanca’s House, summoned by the \nMother’s Heart (page 107). At the beginning of the next Scene, Blanca heals all her Wounds. She starts each Scene as Intangible . If she \nacts to harm a living subject (inflicting 1 Wound, grabbing them, and \nsimilar actions), she becomes Tangible for the rest of the Scene. Once \nper Scene, Blanca can choose to become Intangible again.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I will bring seven children into the water. They will become \nmy children.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639868,"modifiedTime":1781557639868,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"H7fUQrttoyvGsqwY","name":"Flora the Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ypatUbBQ7MZzZerI","name":"Flora the Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208.","positive":"I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1Ponqv2CmCwBHTZB","name":"Gift - Power of the Shard","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MqonqGzY2iuxRawH","name":"Gift - Plant Witch","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Flora can manipulate nearby plants \nby animating them, and thanks to this power, she can perform up to 2 actions in the Exchange with a range equal to \nthe ground covered by the plants themselves. Through the \nplants, Flora can attempt to injure, immobilize, or manipulate a target.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kYsKl3bdAPz25P2t","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch. \nAgenda: To gain the respect of others through my powers \nand live a comfortable life. \nShard Descriptor: I am a clumsy witch who loves \nplants, but unfortunately I have forgotten how to take care \nof my beloved greenhouse. I am humble and don’t care what \nothers think of me, because all I want is to speak to the hearts \nof plants. \nShard Agenda: Take care of my greenhouse and keep \naway any pests that come after me. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda. \nGift - Plant Witch: Flora can manipulate nearby plants \nby animating them, and thanks to this power, she can perform up to 2 actions in the Exchange with a range equal to \nthe ground covered by the plants themselves. Through the \nplants, Flora can attempt to injure, immobilize, or manipulate a target. \nInformation: If the Hunters succeed in removing the \nShard from Flora’s eye, the old witch will come to her \nsenses, but the effects of the Shard will have permanent \nconsequences for her. Drained of all magical power, the \nold woman will try to bargain with the Hunters for the information she possesses in exchange for being exonerated \nof all charges. Flora will then talk about Gerda and Kay’s \nplan, as described in The story that led us here. Flora will \nnot know the location of Lady Storm’s castle, as its entrance \nis protected by powerful magic. However, she will tell the \nHunters that if they continue along the river bordering \nBergen, they can reach the small White Hospital: a facility \nwhere Gerda and Kay reside when they leave the castle. To \nget there, Flora will tell the Hunters to look for the Black \nFeather boat in the small river port of Bergen.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters decide to meet the Black \nFeathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION \nB - Lene’s House. If they decide to leave directly instead, go \nto the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the Black Feathers.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208.","owner":"Flora the Witch","source":"A Frozen Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-flora-the-witch-208","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":208,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch. \nAgenda: To gain the respect of others through my powers \nand live a comfortable life. \nShard Descriptor: I am a clumsy witch who loves \nplants, but unfortunately I have forgotten how to take care \nof my beloved greenhouse. I am humble and don’t care what \nothers think of me, because all I want is to speak to the hearts \nof plants. \nShard Agenda: Take care of my greenhouse and keep \naway any pests that come after me. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda. \nGift - Plant Witch: Flora can manipulate nearby plants \nby animating them, and thanks to this power, she can perform up to 2 actions in the Exchange with a range equal to \nthe ground covered by the plants themselves. Through the \nplants, Flora can attempt to injure, immobilize, or manipulate a target. \nInformation: If the Hunters succeed in removing the \nShard from Flora’s eye, the old witch will come to her \nsenses, but the effects of the Shard will have permanent \nconsequences for her. Drained of all magical power, the \nold woman will try to bargain with the Hunters for the information she possesses in exchange for being exonerated \nof all charges. Flora will then talk about Gerda and Kay’s \nplan, as described in The story that led us here. Flora will \nnot know the location of Lady Storm’s castle, as its entrance \nis protected by powerful magic. However, she will tell the \nHunters that if they continue along the river bordering \nBergen, they can reach the small White Hospital: a facility \nwhere Gerda and Kay reside when they leave the castle. To \nget there, Flora will tell the Hunters to look for the Black \nFeather boat in the small river port of Bergen.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters decide to meet the Black \nFeathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION \nB - Lene’s House. If they decide to leave directly instead, go \nto the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the Black Feathers.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To gain the respect of others through my powers \nand live a comfortable life. \nShard Descriptor: I am a clumsy witch who loves \nplants, but unfortunately I have forgotten how to take care \nof my beloved greenhouse. I am humble and don’t care what \nothers think of me, because all I want is to speak to the hearts \nof plants. \nShard Agenda: Take care of my greenhouse and keep \naway any pests that come after me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Hnu9xe8PVx6QbmlC","name":"The Black Cat","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"BktaJxI8qe1Eaize","name":"The Black Cat - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Black Cat","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","positive":"I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Black Cat","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"J0XvMSJe98SLDFu4","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Black Cat","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying. \nAgenda: Have the humans help me retrieve Britta’s three \nitems. \nFirst Reset: The Cat will observe the Hunters in the \nHeidelberg Entrance Plaza to understand why they are not \naffected by the Magic Tinderbox. It will then go \nto one of the Places to retrieve Britta’s items. \nSecond Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has already \nbeen found, the Cat will take the Hunters to \none of the Places to retrieve the items. The \nCat will also have retrieved one of the items if \nthe Hunters have not already done so.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","owner":"The Black Cat","source":"The Last Wish","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-the-black-cat-136","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":136,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying. \nAgenda: Have the humans help me retrieve Britta’s three \nitems. \nFirst Reset: The Cat will observe the Hunters in the \nHeidelberg Entrance Plaza to understand why they are not \naffected by the Magic Tinderbox. It will then go \nto one of the Places to retrieve Britta’s items. \nSecond Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has already \nbeen found, the Cat will take the Hunters to \none of the Places to retrieve the items. The \nCat will also have retrieved one of the items if \nthe Hunters have not already done so.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Have the humans help me retrieve Britta’s three \nitems. \nFirst Reset: The Cat will observe the Hunters in the \nHeidelberg Entrance Plaza to understand why they are not \naffected by the Magic Tinderbox. It will then go \nto one of the Places to retrieve Britta’s items. \nSecond Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has already \nbeen found, the Cat will take the Hunters to \none of the Places to retrieve the items. The \nCat will also have retrieved one of the items if \nthe Hunters have not already done so.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Hr3BUUFRPYkTC39R","name":"Sultan’s Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"q5CsxYCx7w8VuQCq","name":"Sultan’s Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sultan’s Guards","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and \nwith our warrior skills we protect our lord. \nThe Executioner</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166.","positive":"We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and \nwith our warrior skills we protect our lord. \nThe Executioner","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Sultan’s Guards","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IoEglam1B5yhCltV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sultan’s Guards","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and \nwith our warrior skills we protect our lord. \nThe Executioner</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166.","owner":"Sultan’s Guards","source":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,